</Fragment>

<CommercialHero
  title="Charbroiler Grease Trap and Drain Issues, Same-Day Service"
  subtitle={`Grease pan overflow, drain clog, trap door mechanism. Health Department + LA Fire Marshal compliance. Vulcan, Wolf Range, MagiKitch'n, Garland. $120 commercial. ${phone}`}
  heroImageTitle="Charbroiler Grease Trap Service"
  showBranches={true}
/>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Grease management diagnostic</p>
    <h2>Half of grease-trap calls resolve at scheduling, not appliance repair.</h2>

    <p>Charbroiler grease management failures fall into two categories. <strong>Operational</strong> failures (about 50 percent of calls) come from scheduling issues: grease pan not emptied at appropriate intervals, mid-service capacity exceeded, drain channels not cleaned per recommended schedule. These resolve at customer education plus documented PM scheduling, not parts replacement. <strong>Mechanical</strong> failures (the other 50 percent) come from real component issues: drain channel carbon clogs, trap door motor burnout (auto-clean models), trap door seal failure, grease pan corrosion year 5+.</p>

    <p>Beyond restaurant operations, this work has compliance stakes. <strong>LA County Department of Public Health</strong> requires functional grease management as part of commercial cooking inspection. <strong>California Fire Code (CFC) Chapter 6</strong> plus LA County Fire Department local amendments require functional grease management as part of Ansul or equivalent fire suppression certification. Non-functional grease management voids the fire suppression certification, which can void the kitchen's certificate of occupancy. Annual PM with documented service file is significantly cheaper than reactive repair when Fire Marshal red-tags the operation.</p>

    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. <strong>BHGS #A49573</strong>. <strong>EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410</strong>. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. Parent: <a href="/commercial/charbroiler-repair/">commercial charbroiler repair</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Field observations</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Top causes of grease management issues by frequency.</h2>
    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Grease pan overflow during service (scheduling issue, ~50 percent of calls).</strong> Pan not emptied at appropriate mid-service interval. Resolution: customer education + PM scheduling. No parts replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Drain channel carbon clog (year 2+ restaurant duty).</strong> Carbon deposits + grease solidification redirect grease to wrong path. Cleaning service $180-340.</li>
      <li><strong>Drain channel heat cracking (year 5+).</strong> Spot weld or section replacement $260-480.</li>
      <li><strong>Trap door motor burnout (auto-clean models, year 5-8).</strong> $260-440 motor replacement on Wolf Range Commercial, premium Garland, premium MagiKitch'n.</li>
      <li><strong>Trap door seal failure (heat-warped or grease-coated).</strong> $180-280 reseal service.</li>
      <li><strong>Auto-clean control board failure.</strong> $480-680 replacement on premium auto-clean systems.</li>
      <li><strong>Grease pan corrosion / warping (year 5+).</strong> Pan replacement $180-340.</li>
      <li><strong>Pan capacity inadequate for new menu volume.</strong> Larger-capacity pan replacement, less common, $260-480.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Compliance framework</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Health Department + Fire Marshal coordination.</h2>
    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>LA County DPH inspection.</strong> Functional grease management with documented cleaning schedule. We provide service documentation directly into the customer's HD compliance file format.</li>
      <li><strong>California Fire Code Chapter 6.</strong> Functional grease management as part of Ansul fire suppression certification. Non-functional grease management voids fire suppression cert.</li>
      <li><strong>LA Fire Marshal local amendments.</strong> Specific to LA County and city of Los Angeles, additional requirements on documented annual service. We coordinate inspection scheduling on PM contracts.</li>
      <li><strong>Certificate of occupancy implications.</strong> Voided fire suppression cert from non-functional grease management can void kitchen CO.</li>
      <li><strong>Insurance coverage implications.</strong> Restaurant insurance carriers (Cincinnati, Liberty Mutual, Travelers, the major restaurant carriers) require documented annual service on grease-producing equipment for coverage on grease fire claims.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Honest opinion</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">PM contract is much cheaper than red-tag repair.</h2>
    <p>The single highest-leverage move on charbroiler grease management is annual PM contract with documented service file. Cost: $480 to $1,400 per year depending on equipment count and complexity. Alternative: reactive call when Fire Marshal red-tags the operation, which costs the emergency repair fee ($800 to $2,000), the lost service days while red-tagged (variable but typically $5,000 to $20,000 in lost revenue per day on a busy LA restaurant), and the documentation overhead to satisfy Fire Marshal recertification (usually $1,000 to $3,000 in our consulting and service time). Math is obvious: PM is cheaper. We recommend it because it's what we'd do for our own restaurant.</p>
  </div>
</section>

